Package org.opengis.wrapper.proj4

Class PJFactory.Transform

  • Object
    • PJFactory
      • Transform
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MathTransformFactory, Factory
    Enclosing class:
    PJFactory
    public static class PJFactory.Transform
extends PJFactory
implements MathTransformFactory
    A factory for Math Transform objects created from a list of parameters.

    The only supported methods are:

    • getAvailableMethods(Class)
    • getDefaultParameters(String) - only partially implemented
    • createParameterizedTransform(ParameterValueGroup)
    • createAffineTransform(Matrix)
    • createConcatenatedTransform(MathTransform, MathTransform)
    All other methods unconditionally throw a FactoryException, or return null when doing so is allowed.
    Since:
    3.1

      • getDefaultParameters

        public ParameterValueGroup getDefaultParameters​(String method)
        Returns the parameter group for the given projection. The method argument can be the Proj.4 projection name, or one of its aliases. This method does not check the validity of the given argument, and the returned group does not enumerate the actual list of valid parameters, because Proj.4 does not supply this information.
        Specified by:
        getDefaultParameters in interface MathTransformFactory

      • createAffineTransform

        public MathTransform createAffineTransform​(Matrix matrix)
                                    throws FactoryException
        Creates an affine transform from a matrix. If the transform input dimension is M, and output dimension is N, then the matrix will have size [N+1][M+1]. The [i][N] element of the matrix must be 0 for i less than M, and 1 for i equals M.
        Specified by:
        createAffineTransform in interface MathTransformFactory
        Parameters:
        matrix - the matrix used to define the affine transform.
        Returns:
        the affine transform.
        Throws:
        FactoryException - if the object creation failed.

      • createConcatenatedTransform

        public MathTransform createConcatenatedTransform​(MathTransform transform1,
                                                 MathTransform transform2)
                                          throws FactoryException
        Creates a transform by concatenating two existing transforms. A concatenated transform acts in the same way as applying two transforms, one after the other.

        This implementation can only concatenate two affine transforms, or to Proj.4 transforms. All other cases are unsupported.

        Specified by:
        createConcatenatedTransform in interface MathTransformFactory
        Parameters:
        transform1 - the first transform to apply to points.
        transform2 - the second transform to apply to points.
        Returns:
        the concatenated transform.
        Throws:
        FactoryException - if the object creation failed.
